woke up and screwed up his eyes, not realizing immediately where he was, but at that moment the taxi came to a halt and his wife said softly 'Luzhin, we're home.'

In the elevator he stood smiling and blinking, somewhat dazed but not in the least drunk, and looked at the row of buttons, one of which his wife pressed. 'Quite a way up,' he said and looked at the elevator ceiling, as if expecting to see the summit of their journey. The elevator stopped, 'Hic,' said Luzhin and dissolved into quiet l